cking Attacks on Google are only little examples of security Threatsattacks. Support Vector Machine (SVM), Naive Bayes, Decision Tree, Logistic Regression, and Ensemble approaches can be used to detect this Threatsattack in the cloud and these are the machine learning algorithms. We have primarily concentrated on various security threats, cloud-based attacks, and the methods used to identify these Threatsattacks in this work.','Umma Khatuna Jannat, M.Mohnakumar',36,'submissions/220850_KARPAGAM-JCS_NOV-TO-DEC_2021_ARTICLE-7-PROOF-2.pdf','A Review Of Cloud Computing Security: Threats Attacks and Algorithms'),(866,'2024-09-12','your-doi-here',NULL,107,'Arabic handwritten character recognition is one of the challenging tasks in the field of Natural Language Processing. Currently there are so many English recognition methods. But due to the diversity in Arabic character\'s position and shapes, there are only few Natural Language Processing metods available for Arabic Language. This research paper is an attempt to study various algorithms used for Arabic handwritten character recognition. Latin script OCR is a well-researched area. Arabic script OCR is an emerging area of intense research that follows few reasons: Firstly, around 200 million people in the world use Arabic as their first language. Secondly, around 1.6 billion people follow Islam wherein it is compulsory to recite the religious scripture which was revealed in Arabic. Thirdly, after achieving considerable success in Latin Text OCR, researchers have now focused on extending their prowess to the more challenging Arabic text OCR. Hand written character recognition using many methods like Support Vector Machine analysis algorithm, K Nearest algorithm, Bioinspired alogorithm like artificial neural networks and convolutional neural networks etc. [1,2,3] In this study, preprocessing, feature extraction and post processing methods are focused.','Ashiq V M, E J Thomson Fredrik',48,'submissions/220850_KARPAGAM-JCS_NOV-TO-DEC_2021_ARTICLE-6.pdf','A Survey on Techniques Used in Arabic Handwritten Character Recognition'),(867,'2024-09-12','your-doi-here',NULL,107,'R.Santhosh, Agneeshwaran.G, Arun Arumugam.D, Deepak. V','R.Santhosh, Agneeshwaran.G, Arun Arumugam.D, Deepak. V',44,'submissions/220850_KARPAGAM-JCS_NOV-TO-DEC_2021_ARTICLE-5.pdf','Redtacton Based Health Monitoring System'),(868,'2024-09-12','your-doi-here',NULL,107,'Illuming a virtual world of gaming as an illusion or mirage. Illuming is a prototype that acts as a device replicating the images and creating an object right opposite, which breaks the barrier between the Real and Virtual worlds. This leads to the pathway in transforming the industry from Classical Computing to Quantum Computing using Qubits in the processing unit. Using the power of quantum computing channelizes the processing power to the Quantum algorithms to process the inputs to have a variety of outputs rather than having one descried outcome which is part of classical computing. Modifying the current Figure 1. CPU, GPU, FPGA, and ASIC processing to route it through quantum algorithms which helps us to get the realities outcome that is equivalent to the physical world. This helps us in deriving mixed reality using the current processor.','V. Prasanna Sree Hari, D. Shanmuga Priyaa',43,'submissions/220850_KARPAGAM-JCS_NOV-TO-DEC_2021_ARTICLE-4.pdf','A Survey on Quantum Computing the Game Changer in Gaming Industry-Illuming using Qubits'),(869,'2024-09-12','your-doi-here',NULL,107,'The current examination explores the effect of gold nanoparticles in the pulsatile stream of Casson nanofluid between two endless long equal plates installed in a permeable medium with hall current and ion slip. Administering conditions are developed and changed into common differential conditions utilizing similarity changes. The effect of different parameters is shown through diagrams, and aims to analyze in detail.','M.Jannath Begam, M.Deivanayaki',51,'submissions/220850_KARPAGAM-JCS_NOV-TO-DEC_2021_ARTICLE-3.pdf','The Impact of Gold Nanoparticles in the Pulsatile Flow of Casson Nanofluid with Hall Effect and ion slip through a Porous Medium'),(871,'2024-09-12','your-doi-here',NULL,107,'These learning difficulties are due to genetic and/or life science factors that alter brain function in a way that affects one or more processes related to psychological characteristics of learners. These problems hinder the process of learning basic skills such as reading and writing or math, etc. Also they will additionally interfere with high- level skills such as ranking, time design, abstract design, long-term or short-term memory, and so on. It is necessary to know that learning difficulties have an influence on each person\'s life in addition to academics and can affect family members, friends and even the work itself. This paper aim\'s to put forward some data extraction tools that predict learning disability in children of school age. Decision Tree is a powerful tool that used for data classification and data mining methods. The aim is to achieve better performance and success more effectively by effectively using the technical tools of education, which will deliver a change to students, faculty and academic institutions.','Anu P J, Angeline Prasanna G',56,'submissions/220850_KARPAGAM-JCS_NOV-TO-DEC_2021_ARTICLE-2.pdf','Introduction of Decision Tree Technique of Data Mining to Predict Learning Disability in School- Age Students'),(882,'2024-09-12','your-doi-here',NULL,107,'Composition Graphics of Intuitionistic Fuzzy Ideal of MT Groups in Near Rings','S K Mala, M.M.Shanmugapriya',57,'submissions/220850_KARPAGAM-JCS_NOV-TO-DEC_2021_ARTICLE-1_a4sqokH.pdf','Composition Graphics of Intuitionistic Fuzzy Ideal of MT Groups in Near Rings'),(885,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,122,'The simultaneous effect of vertical ac electric field, vertical temperature gradient, and uniform internal heating on the onset of convection in a dielectric fluid layer is investigated. It is established that the principle of exchange of stability is valid and the resulting eigenvalue problem is solved numerically using the Galerkin method. It is found that the presence of both internal heating as well as vertical ac electric field is to reinforce each other to hasten the onset of convection as compared to their action in isolation. Besides, increase in the value of dimensionless heat source strength and electric Rayleigh number is to reduce the size of convection cells.','I.S.Shivakumara,N.Rudraiah and K.Hemalatha',0,'submissions/article-8.pdf','Electrothermoconvection in a Dielectric Fluid Layer in the Presence of Heat Generation'),(886,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,122,'A Cayley graph is a graph constructed out of a group I and its generating set A. In this paper we attempt to find distance-g dominating sets in Cayley graphs constructed out of Zn. Actually we find the value of distance-g domination num- ber for Cay(Zn, A) where A is generating set of Z. Further we have proved that Cay(Zn, A) is distance-g excellent. We have also shown that Cay(Zn, A) is distance-92-excellent if and only if nt(g/A+1)+1 for some positive integer t. Also we proved that some Cayley graphs are distance-g2-restricted.','T.Tamizh Chelvam,L.Barani Kumar,Sivagnanam Mutharasu.',0,'submissions/article-7.pdf','Distance-g Domination in Cayley Graphs'),(888,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,122,'In this paper we study the linear stability of parallel couple stress viscous fluid flow (CSVF) in a channel and estimate the eigenvalues, c, belonging to the solutions of Orr-Sommerfeld equation for couple stress fluid using energy method. It is shown that CSVF causes inhomogenety in the material science processes which is shown that these inhomogeneties can be controlled by understanding the effect of couple stress on the nature of eigenvalues in the presence of a shear due to horizontal basic velocity. The conditions for the nature of stability of parallel CSVF is determined in terms of couple stress parameter A. An upper bound for the growth rate ci is obtained and from this sufficient conditions for stability (< 0), instability (> 0) and neutral stability (c1 = 0) are obtained, with or without using Schwartz\'s inequality.','N.Rudraiah,B.M.Shankar',0,'submissions/article-6_51NUKDD.pdf','Stability of Parallel Couple Stress Viscous Fluid Flow in a Channel'),(890,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,122,'The generalized dispersion model to study the dispersion of aerosols as the mixture of deformable agglomeration (i.e.solid phase) and coalescence (i.e. fluid phase) of aerosols in the atmosphere is analyzed. A proper theory is developed assuming this mixture behaves as a sparsely packed atmospheric turbulent fluid saturated porous medium.Analytical solutions for velocity are obtained using a regular perturbation technique and concentration distribution is determined using the advection of con- centration by the atmospheric turbulent fluid. It is shown that the aerosols are dispersed relative to a plane moving with the mean speed of atmospheric turbulent fluid with a relative diffusion coefficient, K2(7) Pe-2. This is numerically com- puted and the results reveal that K2(7) Pe-2 increases with an increase in R4 but decreases with an increase in o. This decrease in K2(7) Pe-2, with an increase in sigma and R4 is shown to be favorable for the formation of cloud in the atmosphere.','N.Rudraiah,N.Devaraju	',0,'submissions/article-5_RExhqva.pdf','Generalized Dispersion of Atmospheric Aerosols Using Dusty Fluid and Mixture Theory Models	'),(891,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,122,'A first vacation queue is analyzed using a general approach based on Zadeh\'s Asion principle. Probability generating function for the number of customers derived in fuzzy environment for this queuing model, whose arrival process is Poisson, service time distribution and vacation time are fuzzy functions. Particular cases are deduced.','R.Kalyanaraman,N.Thillaigovindan, G.kannadasan	',0,'submissions/article-4.pdf','A Single Server Vacation Queue with Fuzzy Service Time and Vacation Time Distributions	'),(892,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,122,'We consider a single server retrial queue in which the server is subject to service interruptions with auto repeat facilities and equipped with the mechanism of search of customers from the orbit. The customer whose service is interrupted rejoins the orbit with some known probability or leaves the system with the complementary probability. At the departure epoch, ie., the epoch at which the server becomes free either by a successful service completion or by a service interruption, the server goes in search of customers in the orbit with some probability or remains idle with the complementary probability. Search time is assumed to be negligible. Steady state analysis is performed. Several performance measures that help in efficient design of such systems, are computed. Some numerical illustrations are provided.','A.Krishnamoorthy,Viswanath, C.Narayanan,V.C.Joshua, T.G.Deepak.	',0,'submissions/article-3.pdf','An MAP/PH/1 Retrial Queue with Service Interruption and Orbital Search	'),(894,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,122,'In this paper another proof has been given for a result proved by F. Vajzovic and later by K. Lajk.','PL.Kannappan	',0,'submissions/article-2_MOKTVOD.pdf','On Some Functional Equations	'),(895,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,122,'A mathematical modelling of an inventory system with a single server, operating under stochastic environment is carried out in this work. It is assumed that demand times form a Poisson process. The (s. S) ordering policy is implemented with random lead time. The server goes on to vacation if there is no items in the stock. A customer who arrives during the server vacation period, is offered a choice of leaving the system or joining a pool which is of finite capacity. The customers from the pool will be selected only when the inventory level is more than the reorder level, viz, s. The joint probability distribution of the inventory level and the number of customers in the pool is obtained in the steady state case. Various system performance measures in the steady state are derived and the long-run total expected cost rate is calculated. The results are illustrated numerically.','G.Arivarignan and R.Jayaraman	',0,'submissions/article-1.pdf','Stochastic Modelling of Inventory Systems With Postponed Demands and Multiple Server Vacations	'),(898,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,123,'Boundary value problem for fourth order difference equation is investigated and a theorem for the existence of solutions for the above problem is obtained.','P.U.Chopode,K.L.Bondar,S.T.Patil, V.C.Borkar',0,'submissions/article-1-1_wSeff2X.pdf','Existence of Extremal Solutions for Functional Difference Equation'),(899,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,123,'The effect of chemical reaction rate on the transfer of chemically reactive species in the laminar flow of Newtonian fluid over a stretching sheet immersed in a porous medium is considered. The flow is caused due to unsteady stretching sheet and reactive species is emitted from this sheet which undergoes an isothermal and homogeneous reaction as it diffuses into the surrounding fluid. A diffusion equation with a chemical reaction source term is taken into account. The governing time-dependent nonlinear boundary layer equations are converted into a system of non-linear ordinary differential equations by using similarity transformations. The resulting bounary value problem is solved numerically by applying Runge-Kutta-Fehlberg method with shooting technique. The effects of various physical parameters on mass transfer coefficient are presented graphically. Numerical computations show that the mass transfer depends strongly on the Schmidt number and reaction rate parameter. It is found that the concentration distribution decreases with an increase in the value of unsteadiness parameter, Schmidt number and reaction rate parameter. Further, concentration distribution increases with increase in the order of the chemical reaction. The increase in the concentration boundary layer diminishes for higher chemical reaction order.','Dulal Pal,I.S.Shivakumara	',0,'submissions/article-2-1.pdf','Heat And Mass Transfer In the Boundary Layer Over An Unsteady Sretching Sheet In a Porous Medium	'),(903,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,123,'In this paper, we introduce the notions of fuzzy subnear-ring and fuzzy ideal of near-rings and find more generalized concepts than those introduced by others. The characterization of such fuzzy ideals are also obtained.','R.Ezhilarasi, S.Sriram	',0,'submissions/article-3-1_HyYZZqj.pdf','Fuzzy Subnear-Rings and Fuzzy Ideals of Near-Rings	'),(904,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,123,'In this paper we analyze a GI/M/1 queue with working vacation, in which the server works at different rate rather than completely stopping the service during vacation periods. Baba investigated a GI/M/1 queue with multiple working vacations. They have formulated the queueing system as an embedded two dimensional Markov chain by choosing the arrival epoch as embedded points. Using the algorithmic approach Neutus and others derived the steady state distributions for the number of customers in the system both at arrival and arbitrary epochs and for the sojourn time for an arbitrary customer. Thus the purpose of this paper is to analyze GI/M/1 queueing model under single server working vacation and derived the equilibrium distribution of system size at pre arrival epoch by solving the difference equations using operator technique. Further the expected queue length and various performance measures are obtained in a closed form. Finally special cases are also deduced.','K.Julia Rose Mary, M.I.Afthab Begum	',0,'submissions/article-4-1.pdf','GI/M/1 Queue with Multiple Working Vacation	'),(906,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,123,'Necessary and sufficient conditions for a I-incline to be regular are obtained. It is proved that every commutative regular I-incline is a distributive lattice. Characterizations of the generalized inverses of an element in a P-incline are obtained as a generalization and development of regular elements in an incline.','AR.Meenakshi and S.Anbalagan	',0,'submissions/article-5-1_KS2yCSh.pdf','Regular Elements in a Incline	'),(907,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,123,'In this paper, a special type of ordering for k - regular fuzzy matrices is introduced as a generalization of the minus partial ordering for regular fuzzy matrices. A set of equivalent conditions for a pair of kregular matrices to be under this ordering are obtained. We exhibit that this ordering is preserved under similarity relation.','AR.Meenakshi and P.Poongodi	',0,'submissions/article-6-1.pdf','Orderings on Generalized Regular Fuzzy Matrices	'),(908,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,123,'We define a new f-morphism between two fuzzy graphs. This f-morphism is defined on two scale factors, one based on the scaling of weights of the vertices and the other on the scaling of weights of the edges. We prove that, the relation \"f-morphic\" is an equivalence relation in the collection of fuzzy graphs. We prove that under this f-morphism, the image of an effective edge is an effective edge, the images of fuzzy tree, fuzzy cycle remain as fuzzy tree and fuzzy cycle. We also prove if G,, G, are two fuzzy graphs which are f-morphic then Gi and G2 are also f-morphic.','P.V.Ramakrishnan, M.Vaidyanathan	',0,'submissions/article-7-1.pdf','f-Morphisms in Fuzzy Graphs	'),(909,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,123,'A class of statistical models is proposed where random effects are incorporated into a stochastic differential equations model and an expression for the likelihood function is derived. In general, though, it is not possible to find an explicit expression for the likelihood function, but in a very simple example it is derived and explicit maximum likelihood estimators are found.','K.M.Ramesh Kumar, P.K.Chennaiappan	',0,'submissions/article-8-1.pdf','Random Effects In Stochastic Differential Equation Models	'),(910,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,123,'The purpose of this paper is to introduce the notion of fuzzy strong n-inner product space as a generalization of fuzzy n-inner product space. Ascending family of stronga-n-inner products corresponding to fuzzy strong n-inner product is introduced and we provide some results on it. Key words and phrases: n-inner product, fuzzy n-inner product, fuzzy strong n-inner product, a -n inner product.','N.Rudraiah, G.Chandrasekara	',0,'submissions/article-9-1.pdf','Kelvin- Helmholtz instability at an interface between couple stress fluid and fluid saturated porous layer of large extent	'),(911,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,123,'In this paper, the fuzzy topology induced by n-fuzzy proximity is defined and a relation between the topologies induced by n-fuzzy proximity and its extension is obtained.','K. Sivagamasundari	',0,'submissions/article-10.pdf','N fuzzy proximity-III fuzzy topology induced by n fuzzy proximity	'),(915,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,123,'Convective heat transfer inside an enclosure with double discrete heaters and exit configurations','Sumon Saha, Goutam Saha, Md Quamrul islam, M.C.Raju	',0,'submissions/article-11_otjqplG.pdf','Convective heat transfer inside an enclosure with double discrete heaters and exit configurations'),(916,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,124,'Some common fixed point theorems for Banach operator pair have been presented. These results are proved without the assumption of compatibility, noncompatibility, commutativity and weak commutativity. Caristi\'s fixed point theorems have been generalized.','P.U. Chapode, K L Bondar, V C Borkar , S.T. Patil	',0,'submissions/article-1-2.pdf','Common fixed points for Banach operator pairs	'),(917,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,124,'In this paper, the concept of supremum fuzzy topology denoted by 8 is introduced as the largest fuzzy topology containing the fuzzy topology 8.It is proved that the nth order approximation of the fuzzy topologies 8 and 8 are identical. Some basic and continuous properties of 8\'are discussed. Key Words: Fuzzy topology, nth upper approximation of a fuzzy set, finite fuzzy topology, supremum fuzzy topology, fuzzy continuous functions.','P Jayalakshmi	',0,'submissions/article-2-2.pdf','Fuzzy continuous mappings and finite approximations	'),(918,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,124,'In this paper we deal with matrix ideals, that is, ideals whose elements are matrices over an incline R and we have proved that Pm over P is a matrix ideal as a semiring structure of R over R when P is an ideal of R and Pis a matrix prime ideal, whenever P is a prime ideal of an incline R. Further, we introduce the relation for matrices over an incline as an extension of the relation for elements in an incline with respect to an ideal of an incline. We have proved that the relation between a pair of matrices over an incline, with respect to an ideal of an incline is preserved for their row spaces and column spaces.','AR.Meenakshi, N.Jeyabalan	',0,'submissions/article-3-2.pdf','Matrix Prime Ideals Over an incline	'),(919,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,124,'The interaction of heat transfer with peristaltic transport of a Newtonian fluid through a porous medium in an asymmetric channel in the presence of magnetic field under the assumptions of long wavelength and low Reynolds number is studied. The expressions for velocity field, temperature filed and pressure rise per one wavelength are obtained analytically. The effects of various emerging parameters on the temperature field and pumping characteristics are discussed through graphs.','K.V. Nageswaran reddy ,B. Rama Bhupal Reddy, S.Ramakrishna	',0,'submissions/article-4-2.pdf','Magneto- hydrodynamic peristaltic transport through a porous medium in an asymmetric channel With heat transfer	'),(923,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,124,'In this paper, we investigate the effect of magnetic field on fully developed laminar free convection between vertical plates heated asymmetrically, on taking in to account the uniform wall temperatures, under the influence of transverse magnetic field. The numerical solutions are shown to approach asymptotically the closed form solution for fully developed flow. It is observed that the velocity decreases with the increase of magnetic field parameter M1 for fixed r1 and the velocity increases as r, increases for fixed magnetic parameter M. It is observed that the minimum temperature is shifted towards centre of the channel as r1 increases for fixed M and for fixed r1=0 the pressure values are decreasing with increasing M. Nusselt number decreases with increase in magnetic parameter.','B.Rama Bhupal Reddy, S.Ramakrishna	',0,'submissions/article-5-2_CUzxCKc.pdf','The Effect of Magnetic Field on Fully Developed Laminar Free Convection between Vertical Plates Heated Asymmetrically	'),(924,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,124,'Since the introduction of public-key cryptography by Diffe and Hellman in 1976, the potential for the use of the discrete logarithm problem in public-key cryptosystems has been recognized. Although the discrete logarithm problem as first employed by Diffe and Hellman was defined explicitly as the problem of finding logarithms with respect to a generator in the multiplicative group of the integers module a prime, this idea can be extended to arbitrary groups and in particular, to elliptic curve groups. The resulting public - key systems provide relatively small block size, high speed, and high security. In this paper, a vector space secrets sharing scheme is proposed in detail. Its security is based on the security of ECC. This scheme has the following characteristic: the precondition of (t,n)- threshold secret sharing scheme that all assignees purview must be same is generalized. A verifiable infrastructure is provided, which can be used to detect the cheaters from the dealers and assignees. The shared key distributed by dealer is encrypted based on ECC, which enhances the security. So this scheme is of less computation cost which is valuable in applications with limited memory, communications bandwidth or computing power.','A.R.Rishivarman, B.Parthasaraathy, M.Thiagarajan	',0,'submissions/article-6-2.pdf','An Elliptic Curve Based Vector space key sharing scheme over GF(2^5)	'),(925,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,124,'The linear stability of parallel couple stress viscous fluid flow through a sparsely packed porous channel using modified Darcy-Brinkman equation, modified in the sense of inclusion of the effect of couple stress, is studied using energy method supplimented with a single term Galerkin expansion. The sufficient condition for stability is obtained using the nature of the growth rate as well as sufficiently small values of the Reynolds number, R. From this condition we show that strengthening or weakening of the stability criterion is dictated by the values of the coefficient of couple stress fluid and the porous parameter.','N.Rudraiah, B.M.Shankar, Krishna B.Chavaraddi	',0,'submissions/article-7-2.pdf','Stability of Parallel Couple Stress Fluid Flow through a Porous Channel	'),(926,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,124,'The purpose of this paper is to introduce the concept of normal fuzzy biclosure spaces and investigate some of their characterizations.','U.D.Tapi, R.Navalakhe	',0,'submissions/article-8-2.pdf','Normal Fuzzy Biclosure Spaces	'),(931,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,124,'Fuzzy Strong n-Inner Product Space	','S.Vijayabalaji	',0,'submissions/article-9-2_Tgrdv1y.pdf','Fuzzy Strong n-Inner Product Space	'),(932,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,125,'The paper purports to examine the nature and the interactions between the species in some special cases of a mathematical model of an ecological Ammensal model in which Ammensal (S.) and enemy (S,) species are surviving with unlimited resources. The model is formed by a coupled system of first order non-linear ordinary differential equations. The only one equilibrium point is noticed and the criteria for its stability are inferred. Solutions for the linearised perturbed equations are determined. Further the numerical solutions for this model are computed for identifying the nature and the interactions between the species by using Runge-Kutta method of fourth order.','K.V.L.N. Acharyulu, N.Ch.Pattabhi Ramacharyulu	',0,'submissions/article-1-3.pdf','Special cases in a Mathematical Model of an Ecological Ammensalism with Unlimited resources-A Numerical Study	'),(933,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,125,'Blood being an important constituent of human body have been studied in various ways. Here, its flow have been considered in two phase model of blood flow through narrow tube with viscosity near the walls, blood volumetric flow equation is counted and the shear stress at the walls have been evaluated. Analytical models for flow of blood have been utilized to study the flow in different conditions. A non-Newtonian model has been undertaken by using Cauchy stress tensor to study blood flow and by associating momentum and constitutive equation a new form is being formed. A one dimensional view has been taken by dealing with viscosity and shear rate in the bases of viscometric data which is being carried to find dimensionless momentum equation. Pulsatile nature of blood has been taken which occurs due to pressure by heart beating and by considering various limitations and wave equation has been evaluated.','M.S.Bisht, Amit Singh Negi	',0,'submissions/article-1-3_oImFLah.pdf','Blood Flow in Human Body	'),(934,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,125,'For estimating the population meany of the variable under study y, an almost unbiased estimator has been proposed. The expression for the bias and mean square error of the proposed estimator has been obtained and it has been shown that proposed estimator is unbiased as well as equally efficient with the regression estimator. The comparison of proposed estimator with the regression estimator has also been made upto second order of approximation w.r.t. their biases and mean square errors. The results have also been illustrated numerically.','H.S.Jhajj, Davinder Kumar Garg, Ghansham Mishra	',0,'submissions/article-3-3.pdf','Almost Unbiased Estimator of finite population Mean in survey sampling	'),(935,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,125,'The paper considers an inventory model with backorders in a fuzzy situation by employing the type of fuzzy numbers which are trapezoidal. The EOQ models have been developed using different optimization methods. A full fuzzy model is developed where the input parameters and the decision variables are fuzzified. The optimal policy for the developed model is determined using the Lagrangean conditions after the defuzzification of the cost function with the graded mean integration method. The proposed method finds the optimal lotsize and backorders level considering both linear and fixed backorders costs. Numerical examples are provided to highlight the difference between crisp and the fuzzy cases.','R.Kalaiarasi, W.Ritha	',0,'submissions/article-4-3.pdf','Optimization of EOQ Inventory models with two backorders	'),(936,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,125,'Different methods are proposed for finding the solution of fully fuzzy linear system (FFLS) that is, fuzzy linear system with fuzzy coefficients involving fuzzy variables. All of these existing methods assume the non negativity constraint on the solution. Hence all the methods are designed keeping this restriction prior to their development which is an invalid approach. In this paper, we extend the concept of existing methods to solve FFLS with triangular fuzzy numbers of the form (a,b,c) without assuming any restriction on the solution and hence widen the implementation scope of fuzzy linear systems in several engineering applications and sciences like quantum optics, topological spaces and hyperchaotic systems. The proposed method is illustrated with numerical examples.','A.kumar, N.Babbar, A.Bansal	',0,'submissions/article-5-3.pdf','Solution of Fully Fuzzy Linear system with Triangular Fuzzy Numbers(a,b,c)	'),(943,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,125,'M/M/1 Retrial Queueing system with single working vacation under Non-Pre-Emptive Priority Service	','A.Muthu Gnanpathi Subramanian, G.Ayyappan, Gopal Sekar	',0,'submissions/article-6-3_ruxcrBf.pdf','M/M/1 Retrial Queueing system with single working vacation under Non-Pre-Emptive Priority Service	'),(944,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,125,'The present paper is a study of a new three variable analogue of Hermite polynomials H (x,y,z) whose two variables version seems more natural than that of Hemite polynomials of two variables defined and studied by M.A. Khan and G.S. Abukhammash [1].','Mumtaz Ahmad Khan, Abdul Hakim Khan, Naeem Ahmad	',0,'submissions/article-7-3.pdf','A Note on a new three variable analogue of Hermite Polynomials of II Kind	'),(945,'2024-09-23','your-doi-here',NULL,125,'This paper discusses the use of Aris analysis to study the dispersion of a chiral fluid flow in a channel in the presence of a convective current bounded by porous layers. Analytical solution for velocity in the presence of a transverse magnetic field is obtained and it is computed for different values of electromagnetic number W. Similarly we have found the analytical solution in the presence of advection of concentration distribution of chiral fluid by using Fourier Transform Method by introducing new space coordinates. Following Aris model, measure of the effective dispersion coefficient Dig/D=1+ D for the distribution of chiral fluid which is the sum of the particle diffusivity and the Taylor\'s dispersion coefficient, where D is the Taylor\'s dispersion coefficient. This Dog/