Climate Change','2024-09-17','2024-09-17',40),(10,'submissions/CIA-3-Set2.docx','submissions/DATA_MINING_Ri3TBPC.doc','Artificial Intelligence','Unfair predictions of machine learning (ML) models impede their broad acceptance\r\nin real-world settings. Tackling this arduous challenge first necessitates defining what it\r\nmeans for an ML model to be fair. This has been addressed by the ML community with\r\nvarious measures of fairness that depend on the prediction outcomes of the ML models,\r\neither at the group-level or the individual-level. These fairness measures are limited in that\r\nthey utilize point predictions, neglecting their variances, or uncertainties, making them\r\nsusceptible to noise, missingness and shifts in data. In this paper, we first show that a\r\nML model may appear to be fair with existing point-based fairness measures but biased\r\nagainst a demographic group in terms of prediction uncertainties. Then, we introduce new\r\nfairness measures based on different types of uncertainties, namely, aleatoric uncertainty\r\nand epistemic uncertainty. We demonstrate on many datasets that (i) our uncertaintybased measures are complementary to existing measures of fairness, and (ii) they provide\r\nmore insights about the underlying issues leading to bias.','2024-11-14','2024-11-14',65),(11,'submissions/IEEE_PAPER_vcEzgQ5.docx','submissions/IEEE_PAPER_SOEgI05.docx','NEURAL NETWORKS','This study explores the application of Artificial Neural Networks (ANN) and Finite Element Analysis (FEA) to optimize the properties of concrete mixtures containing Rice Husk Ash (RHA) as a supplementary cementitious material. ANNs are employed for their ability to handle complex, non-linear relationships between input variables like RHA content, water-cement ratio, and curing time, and output properties such as compressive strength. They offer high accuracy in predictive modeling, especially with extensive experimental data, enabling the identification of optimal concrete mixtures. Concurrently, FEA is used to simulate the physical behavior of concrete under stress, providing detailed insights into durability, crack formation, and structural performance over time. This method is particularly effective for analyzing mechanical and structural behaviors, thereby complementing the predictive capabilities of ANNs. By integrating ANN and FEA, the study demonstrates that these models predict concrete properties with greater accuracy and reliability compared to manual methods. This integrated','2024-11-12','2024-11-12',75),(12,'submissions/DATA_MINING_5C0QjK5.doc','submissions/DATA_MINING_41GsaFy.doc',NULL,'','2024-11-12','2024-11-12',77),(13,'submissions/DATA_MINING_6ttMuek.doc','submissions/DATA_MINING_cuTttff.doc','Blockchain Technology: Enhancing Security and Transparency in Digital Transactions','Blockchain Technology: Enhancing Security and Transparency in Digital Transactions','2024-11-12','2024-11-12',8);
