L,NULL,NULL,1,3,3,1,NULL,NULL,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(110,'A survey on predicting and controlling air pollution using Machine learning and deep learning techniques','KJCS-2025-02-4','Since air pollution has a significant negative influence on public health, early warning systems must be able to make precise long-term predictions about air quality. Predicting air quality has garnered a lot of interest, combining computer science, statistics, and environmental science. The Paper reviews a number of studies on air pollution, its effects on mental health, and the use of machine learning methods for air quality monitoring and prediction. Some of the studies investigate the connection between mental health outcomes and air pollution. They draw attention to the substantial influence that air pollutants, especially PM2.5, have on mental health conditions like depression and psychotic episodes. Machine learning techniques are used in many research to forecast pollution levels and air quality. To predict air quality indicators and particular pollutant concentrations, this research uses a variety of models, including Support Vector Machines (SVM), Random Forests, Neural Networks, and ensemble techniques like XGBoost. Innovative methods of environmental monitoring, such as the application of AI, IoT, and computer vision technologies, are the subject of certain studies. These technologies are used in urban settings to identify and categorize different types of pollution, including visual pollution. The combined findings of these studies highlight the substantial harm that air pollution causes to the general public, especially to mental health, and show how cutting-edge technologies can be used to monitor, forecast, and control air quality in metropolitan settings',0,0,0,2514,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'Dear Sir/Mam,\r\n                          I am submitting my paper entitled \"A survey on predicting and controlling air pollution using Machine learning and deep learning techniques\".. Kindly process and publish it. Thanks & Regards!\r\nNinsha V Unnikrishan','2025-02-18','2025-03-26',1,'submissions/merged_submission_110.pdf','\n\nAE Comments:\nReviewers Comments:\n\n\n\nThe presented survey is not adequate and comprehensive. No systematic comparison or evaluation of the state of the art has been carried out.',NULL,'2025-04-02',20,3,99,2,1,15,2,NULL,'2025-03-24',NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/ninsha_1.pdf'),(113,'IoT Based Secure Transaction in Remote Patient Monitoring Using Cryptography Techniques','KJCS-2025-02-5','Remote patient monitoring involves using technology to collect health data from individuals in one location and electronically communicating that information to healthcare sources in aaltered location. This allows healthcare professionals to monitor patients\' conditions remotely. Health data collected by IoT devices are transmitted over the internet. While data transaction, security challenges are faced in remote patient monitoring .Safeguarding sensitive patient information is crucial to prevent from unauthorized access. In this article purpose cryptographic algorithm is used to prevent data during transaction, AES (Advanced Encryption Standard) and Blowfish algorithm is used in a hybrid encryption approach for securing data in remote patient monitoring. In this paper, IoT devices like SPO2 (blood oxygen saturation), temperature, and heart pulse sensors involves the continuous collection and transmission of vital signs from patients to healthcare providers. The integration of wearable devices and a secure remote monitoring system enhances the ability to detect and address medical issues promptly. Using a hybrid encryption approach with both AES and Blowfish can enhance security, mitigate various Cyber Attack and can do secure transaction in IoT. This combination helps protect against attacks such as brute-force attacks, cryptanalysis, and vulnerabilities specific to each algorithm. Additionally, it adds an extra layer of defense by diversifying the encryption methods, making it more challenging for attackers to exploit potential weaknesses in a single algorithm. The implementation result of this hybrid algorithm ensures confidentiality, integrity, authentication and trust in remote patient monitoring systems. In essence, the future of secure transactions in remote patient monitoring lies in a dynamic, adaptive approach that integrates cutting-edge technologies to fortify the overall cyber security posture and safeguard patient data with the highest level of resilience.',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'Please publish my paper in Karpagam journal of computer science.','2025-02-22','2025-02-26',0,'submissions/merged_submission_113.pdf','',NULL,NULL,3,3,101,1,2,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(114,'A study on Dermatological Diagnosis of Cardiovascular Disease Through Multimodal Fusion of Artificial Intelligence','KJCS-2025-02-6','The Incorporation of multimodal Fusion of Artificial Intelligence (AI) has the feasible to improve the Dermatological Diagnosis of Cardiovascular diseases(CVDs). This survey reviews recent advancements in AI techniques that utilize diverse data types, including dermoscopic images, electronic health records (EHRs), to enhance diagnostic accuracy. Drawing from Scopus indexed journals, we present a comprehensive literature review, discuss methodologies and approaches and highlight recent trends in the field. This survey synthesis of knowledge aims to inform future research directions and promote interdisciplinary collaboration.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2025-02-26','2025-02-26',0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,3,91,1,NULL,NULL,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(115,'A Study on Dermatological Diagnosis of Cardiovascular Disease Through Multimodal Fusion of Artificial Intelligence','KJCS-2025-02-7','The incorporation of multimodal fusion of Artificial Intelligence (AI) has the feasible to improve the dermatological diagnosis of cardiovascular diseases (CVDs). This survey reviews recent advancements in AI techniques that utilize diverse data types, including dermoscopic images, electronic health records (EHRs), to enhance diagnostic accuracy. Drawing from Scopus-indexed journals, we present a comprehensive literature review, discuss methodologies and approaches, and highlight recent trends in the field. This synthesis of knowledge aims to inform future research directions and promote interdisciplinary collaboration.',0,0,0,1893,0,0,0,0,0,'-',0,'My Research Paper \"A Study on Dermatological Diagnosis of Cardiovascular Disease Through Multimodal Fusion of Artificial Intelligence\" is my own paper. The main purpose of the research article is to find out the further scope to diagnosis the cardiovascular diseases through Multimodal features using dermatology AI.','2025-02-26','2025-03-10',0,'submissions/merged_submission_115_WekJJWf.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,19,3,91,1,NULL,111,2,NULL,'2025-03-24',NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/albert_v2.pdf'),(116,'MACHINE LEARNING IN INTRUSION DETECTION TRENDS LEARNING AND FUTURE CHALLENGES','KJCS-2025-02-8','AbstractNetworks and information systems must be protected from cyberattacks by intrusion detection systems. Traditional rule-based intrusion detection systems are becoming less and less effective against complex and dynamic threats.  Consequently, machine learning (ML) approaches are being used to create more intelligent, flexible and instantaneous threat detection systems.  The Machine learning approaches utilised in IDS are supervised, unsupervised, ensemble, deep learning and federated learning models which is thoroughly reviewed in this work.  Their benefits, drawbacks and practical uses are highlighted. This study also covers performance evaluation measures, datasets and new developments including edge computing solutions, privacy-preserving intrusion detection systems and Explainable AI (XAI).  The study offers possible remedies while shedding light on problems related to feature selection, class imbalance, scalability and false positives. This research aims to provide researchers and practitioners with a better understanding of recent advancements in IDS models.',0,1,2,2500,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'From \r\nRESMI KRISHNAN V\r\nRRESEARCH SCHOLAR KARPAGAM ACADEMY OF HIGHER EDUCATION COIMBATORE 21\r\nRespected Editor,\r\n\r\nI, Resmi Krishnan V, am pleased to submit my review paper titled \"Machine Learning for Intrusion Detection: Trends, Challenges, and Future Directions\" for consideration for publication in JCS Publication.\r\nI kindly request you to consider my submission for peer review. Please find the manuscript and all necessary documents attached as per the journals guidelines. I look forward to your positive response.\r\n\r\nThank you for your time and consideration','2025-02-28','2025-03-26',1,'submissions/merged_submission_116.pdf','\n\nAE Comments:\nReviewers Comments:\n\n\n\nSurvey is not comprehensive. Revise paper by include more objective.',NULL,'2025-04-02',20,3,109,2,1,15,2,NULL,'2025-03-24',NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/resmi_1.pdf'),(117,'A REVIEW OF DIFFERENT MACHINE LEARNING ALGORITHMS FOR THE DETECTION OF AUTISM SPECTRUM DISORDERS','KJCS-2025-03-1','A developmental disorder that lasts a lifetime, autism is also known as autism spectrum disorder (ASD). It influences how people interact, communicate, and digest information. Any stage of life can be diagnosed with ASD; the disorder grows with age, and the symptoms will be fully present in the first two years. ASD is characterized by difficulties with focus, learning, mobility, and mental health issues like depression and anxiety, among others. Early detection of ASD can lessen the challenges that individuals confront and lower the expense of therapy for the medical community. Because of these difficulties, people with autism experience varying degrees of functional impairment, despite the notion that autism is a lifelong condition. This review article\'s primary goal is to examine the application and significance of several machine learning algorithms for the early diagnosis of autism spectrum disorders.',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'Please Find the Attachment','2025-03-02','2025-03-02',0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,3,114,2,NULL,NULL,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(118,'A REVIEW OF DIFFERENT MACHINE LEARNING ALGORITHMS FOR THE DETECTION OF AUTISM SPECTRUM DISORDERS','KJCS-2025-03-2','A developmental disorder that lasts a lifetime, autism is also known as autism spectrum disorder (ASD). It influences how people interact, communicate, and digest information. Any stage of life can be diagnosed with ASD; the disorder grows with age, and the symptoms will be fully present in the first two years. ASD is characterized by difficulties with focus, learning, mobility, and mental health issues like depression and anxiety, among others. Early detection of ASD can lessen the challenges that individuals confront and lower the expense of therapy for the medical community. Because of these difficulties, people with autism experience varying degrees of functional impairment, despite the notion that autism is a lifelong condition. This review article\'s primary goal is to examine the application and significance of several machine learning algorithms for the early diagnosis of autism spectrum disorders.',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'Please review my paper and publish in Karpagam Journal of Computer Science','2025-03-03','2025-03-05',0,'submissions/merged_submission_118_IpmYWbI.pdf','',NULL,NULL,3,3,114,2,2,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(119,'A Study on Cyber bullying in Social Media Platforms using Machine Learning Techniques','KJCS-2025-03-3','The rapid expansion of online social communities has captured the attention of researchers and academics alike. As more and more human interaction shifts to digital platforms, advancements in mobile and network technologies have facilitated unprecedented connectivity. However, this increased social connectivity has also g