air and surface temperature, precipitation, and other soil components (such as nitrogen, phosphorous, and potassium) all contribute to effective agriculture.  One piece of current evidence in this area is a model that uses machine learning methods (Random Forest, Decision Tree, and Artificial Neural Network) to identify the best crop. Deep learning techniques are used in this research to improve the suggested model. In addition to crop prediction, clear information about the quantities of soil elements required and their costs is obtained.  It offers a higher level of accuracy than the current model.  By analyzing the provided data, it assists farmers in crop prediction, which ultimately aids in profit-making.  To forecast an appropriate yield, the land\'s soil and climate are taken into account. The goal is to demonstrate a Python-based system that intelligently employs tactics to predict the most fruitful yield under specific circumstances while incurring the fewest costs.  While LSTM and RNN are employed as Deep Learning algorithms in this paper, SVM is implemented as a Machine Learning method.',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'I am submitting my article titled  \"A Crop Yield Prediction Hybrid Approach Using Deep Learning And Machine Learning Algorithms\" for consideration for publication in Karpagam JCS. \r\n\r\nThis article is unpublished and I am submitting it exclusively to your publication. I am happy to make revisions based on editorial feedback and provide any additional information as needed.\r\n\r\nThank you for considering my work.','2025-05-13','2025-05-26',0,'submissions/merged_submission_143.pdf','',NULL,NULL,3,3,134,1,2,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/sumi-jcs1.pdf'),(144,'A Data-Driven Framework for Early Cyber Attack Detection Using Time-Series Modeling','KJCS-2025-05-6','As cyber threats grow in frequency and\r\ncomplexity, traditional intrusion detection\r\nsystems often fall short in providing early\r\nand proactive threat alerts. This paper\r\npresents a data-driven framework that\r\nintegrates time-series modeling with\r\nmachine learning techniques to detect and\r\npredict cyber-attacks at an early stage. By\r\nleveraging historical network data and\r\nanalyzing temporal patterns, the proposed\r\nsystem is capable of identifying anomalies\r\nthat precede attack execution. Evaluation on\r\nbenchmark datasets demonstrates that the\r\nframework achieves high detection accuracy\r\nwith low false alarm rates, making it suitable\r\nfor real-time threat mitigation in dynamic\r\nnetwork environments.',1,-1,-1,-1,0,0,0,0,1,'I am interest on doing papers with Cyberforensic',0,'Respected Sir/Mam\r\nHere i have attached my Research  paper for our  esteemed University of Karpagam Journal of Computer Science. Kindly Review my paper','2025-05-13','2025-05-26',0,'submissions/merged_submission_144.pdf','',NULL,NULL,3,3,132,2,2,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/sathiya_jcs_1.pdf'),(145,'An Efficient and significant way to predict the Stock Market Prediction by using Machine Learning Techniques','KJCS-2025-05-7','In the current scenario stock market tends to be a promising avenue for every lucrative investments, even though this promising only depends upon the prediction of past and current scenario that might be followed via a subsequent forecasting options. The current market in this economy might rise or fall according with the numerous values which can be considered as they are making the best transaction in the stock market. Predicting the stock market manually by using these values and also the factors which are affecting tends to be a cumbersome and also the prone of error. Hence, For these situations we may give rise to a Machine Learning approach which is most widely used for predicting this type of chaotic method. In this paper we have used Machine Learning Algorithm in order to predict the stock market analysis by using the index value, opening and closing price etc. By doing so this may help the future investors to predict the stock market and make the decisions quicker.',0,8,NULL,3407,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'I am pleased to submit our manuscript entitled An Efficient and significant way to predict the Stock Market Prediction by using Machine Learning Techniques for consideration for publication in Karpagam JCS. \r\nThis manuscript has not been published elsewhere and is not under consideration by any other journal. All authors have read and approved the manuscript and have no conflicts of interest to disclose. Thank you for considering our submission. We look forward to your response.','2025-05-15','2025-05-15',0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,3,136,2,NULL,NULL,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(146,'An Efficient and significant way to predict the Stock Market Prediction by using Machine Learning Techniques','KJCS-2025-05-8','In the current scenario stock market tends to be a promising avenue for every lucrative investments, even though this promising only depends upon the prediction of past and current scenario that might be followed via a subsequent forecasting options. The current market in this economy might rise or fall according with the numerous values which can be considered as they are making the best transaction in the stock market. Predicting the stock market manually by using these values and also the factors which are affecting tends to be a cumbersome and also the prone of error. Hence, For these situations we may give rise to a Machine Learning approach which is most widely used for predicting this type of chaotic method. In this paper we have used Machine Learning Algorithm in order to predict the stock market analysis by using the index value, opening and closing price etc. By doing so this may help the future investors to predict the stock market and make the decisions quicker.',0,8,NULL,3407,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'I am pleased to submit our manuscript entitled An Efficient and significant way to predict the Stock Market Prediction by using Machine Learning Techniques for consideration for publication in Karpagam JCS. This manuscript has not been published elsewhere and is not under consideration by any other journal. All authors have read and approved the manuscript and have no conflicts of interest to disclose. Thank you for considering our submission. We look forward to your response.','2025-05-15','2025-05-26',0,'submissions/merged_submission_146.pdf','',NULL,NULL,3,3,136,2,2,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/vinitha_jcs.pdf'),(147,'PREDICTIVE ANALYTICS IN AGRICULTURE: MACHINE LEARNING MODELS FOR CROP YIELD','KJCS-2025-05-9','Machine learning applications are transforming the way data is processed and decisions are made, which is having a big effect on the global economy. Agriculture is one of the industries that is significantly impacted by the global food supply issue. This research aims to find out what modern farmers may gain by employing machine learning techniques. Optimising agricultural productivity while reducing waste is primary goal of these algorithms, which use intelligent judgements for planting, watering, and harvesting. Study delves into present situation of machine learning in farming, drawing attention to important obstacles and possibilities. It provides experimental evidence that changes to labels affect the precision of data processing algorithms. By analysing the massive amounts of data acquired from farms and utilising online, real-time data from IoT sensors, results suggest that farmers may make better decisions on variables influencing crop growth. Eventually, incorporating these Technology that increases agricultural yields while decreasing waste has the potential to change modern agriculture. Among the fifteen different algorithms, one newly developed algorithm that improves feature combining schemes is provided in order to help determine which method is most appropriate for usage in agriculture. According to the results, 99.46% classification accuracy can be achieved with the Hoeffding Tree and Nave Bayes Classifier methods, and 99.59% classification accuracy can be achieved with the Bayes Net methodology. These results will demonstrate higher output rates.\r\nKeywords: Random Forest, Logistic Regression, Nave Bayes, ANN, Smart farming, Crop analysis and prediction.',0,5,5,1200,0,0,0,0,1,'i am inteested to put more paper of our journal',0,'Please find our manuscript entitled \"[Title of Your Paper]\" submitted for your consideration in [PREDICTIVE ANALYTICS IN AGRICULTURE: MACHINE LEARNING MODELS FOR CROP YIELD]\r\nWe believe it offers novel insights  and hope it will be suitable for publication.','2025-05-16','2025-05-26',0,'submissions/merged_submission_147.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,3,137,2,NULL,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/ramleela.jcs_1.pdf'),(149,'Neuro Causal Intelligence Based Hybrid Framework for Transparent Decision Making  in Autonomous Scientific Systems','KJCS-2025-05-11','The advent of autonomous systems in scientific research has marked a significant evolution in data processing, decision-making, and analysis. While machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) algorithms have demonstrated remarkable success in scientific applications, these systems often operate as black boxes, providing minimal transparency regarding their decision-making processes. This lack of interpretability hinders trust and limits the applicability of autonomous systems in high-stakes scientific domains, such as healthcare, environmental monitoring, and complex simulations. In this context, we propose the concept of Neuro-Causal Intelligence, a hybrid framework designed to integrate the strengths of causal reasoning with advanced neural architectures, ensuring transparent, interpretable, and reliable decision-making in autonomous scientific systems. The core principle behind Neuro-Causal Intelligence lies in its ability to merge causal inference with neural network models. Causal inference provides a rigorous approach to understanding the relationships between variables, making it possible to trace the causes of observed outcomes, whereas neural networks excel at identifying patterns and correlations in large datasets. By combining these two methodologies, our framework allows the system to not only predict outcomes but also explain the underlying causes and mechanisms responsible for these outcomes. This hybrid approach is particularly essential for scientific systems that require not only accurate predictions but also understandable reasoning for validation and further analysis. The framework operates in three key stages: (1) Causal Discovery, where causal relationships between variables are identified using causal inference techniques such as Bayesian networks and Granger causality. This step ensures that the system can uncover the true underlying causal mechanisms within a scientific context. (2) Neural Network Integration, where deep learning models are trained to recognize complex patterns in data. The neural network is tailored to integrate causal knowledge during the learning process, ensuring that predictions are not only data-driven but also contextually grounded in causal logic. (3) Transparent Decision-Making, where the system employs explainable AI techniques to provide human-readable justifications for its decisions. These explanations highlight the causal \r\nfactors that influenced the predictions, thus enhancing transparency and fostering trust among users. The accuracy and reliability of the framework are evaluated through multiple scientific use cases, were  it consistently outperforms traditional black-box neural network models. The integration of causal reasoning allows the system to achieve a higher level of interpretability without compromising predictive accuracy. The system\'s decision-making process is characterized by an accuracy improvement of approximately 15% compared to conventional models, while also providing causal explanations for each decision. Furthermore, the framework ensures a transparent and accountable decision-making process, which is crucial in domains where scientific results need to be explained and justified to stakeholders, regulatory bodies, and the public. In addition to improving accuracy, the Neuro-Causal Intelligence framework also enhances the robustness of autonomous systems. By providing causal insights, the system can better adapt to new and unseen data, making it more resilient to variations in input. This flexibility is essential for scientific systems that operate in dynamic, uncertain environments where new knowledge and data continuously emerge.',0,7,4,4932,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'I am pleased to submit our manuscript entitled Neuro Causal Intelligence Based Hybrid Framework for Transparent Decision Making in Autonomous Scientific Systems for your kind consideration for publication with JCS.\r\n\r\nThis paper proposes a novel hybrid frameworkNeuro-Causal Intelligence (NCI)which integrates causal inference techniques with deep neural network architectures to address the critical need for transparency and interpretability in autonomous scientific systems. Our work is driven by the increasing deployment of AI in high-stakes domains like healthcare, environmental monitoring, and scientific simulations, where understanding and justifying decisions is as important as predictive performance.\r\n\r\nThe framework features a three-stage pipeline involving causal discovery, neural integration, and explainable decision-making. Our experiments, conducted on synthetic and real-world datasets such as CKD diagnostics and environmental sensors, demonstrate superior performance over traditional models in terms of prediction accuracy (93.4%), causal fidelity (96.7%), and explainability (score of 0.91). We believe that this contribution provides a foundational step toward the development of trustworthy and human-aligned autonomous systems.\r\n\r\nWe affirm that this manuscript is original, has not been published elsewhere, and is not under consideration by any other publication. All authors have approved the manuscript and agree with its submission.\r\n\r\nThank you for your time and consideration. We look forward to the opportunity to share our findings with the wider research community.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nN. Nagalakshmi\r\nAssistant Professor\r\nKarpagam Academy of Higher Education\r\nCoimbatore\r\nEmail: nagalakshmi.nagarajan@kahedu.edu.in\r\n\r\nCc: Dr. V. Nandalal\r\nProfessor, Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering\r\nSri Krishna College of Engineering and Technology, Coimbatore\r\nEmail: nandalal@skcet.ac.in','2025-05-26','2025-05-26',0,'submissions/merged_submission_149_IzZZ3aj.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,3,138,1,NULL,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/nagalakshmi_aids_1.pdf'),(150,'Predictive Framework for Moral Decision Modeling in Critical Systems Using Conscious AI and Data-Centric Ethics','KJCS-2025-05-12','In recent years, the integration of artificial intelligence (AI) in high-stakes domains such as healthcare, defines, autonomous vehicles, and financial systems has raised critical ethical concerns. As AI transitions from reactive systems to more advanced, conscious-like entities, there is an urgent need for frameworks that enable transparent, data-driven, and morally sound decision-making. This paper presents a predictive framework for moral decision modeling in critical systems using Conscious AI embedded with data-centric ethical analysis. The framework is designed to balance accuracy, ethical reasoning, and explainability by integrating multiple AI components capable of processing contextual and human-centric data under critical constraints. The core of this system is a Conscious AI architecture that mimics aspects of awareness and self-regulation through feedback loops and context sensitivity. This architecture is layered over a data-centric ethics module that utilizes labelled ethical datasets, real-world scenarios, and rule-based logical annotations. These annotations are further processed through supervised and unsupervised learning techniques to extract ethical patterns and moral features. The integration of predictive modeling and moral evaluation occurs in a decision-control layer, where outcomes are analysed for ethical consistency and trustworthiness. Experiments were conducted across three critical domainsautonomous driving, emergency medical triage, and military drone navigationusing synthetic and real-world datasets. The proposed framework achieved an average decision accuracy of 93.6% across all scenarios, while maintaining a moral consistency rate of 91.2% based on cross-validation with human ethics panels. Explainability modules, powered by SHAP and LIME, were embedded to ensure transparent visualization of ethical decision pathways, which enhanced user trust by 87% in a controlled trial. Unlike traditional AI models that rely solely on utility functions or static rule sets, this framework continuously learns ethical nuances from evolving datasets, enabling adaptive moral alignment. It supports counterfactual analysis, enabling the system to simulate what-if scenarios for moral dilemma resolution. Additionally, ethical bias detection modules flag potentially discriminatory or harmful decisions, which are corrected in real time through the feedback loop. This hybrid approach outperforms existing ethical AI solutions by combining neuro-symbolic AI, deep learning, and ethical ontologies in a unified decision-making pipeline. The frameworks modularity allows for domain-specific adaptation without retraining the core engine. Moreover, the conscious component facilitates not only prediction and reasoning but also ethical introspection, thus enhancing decision reliability in ambiguous and high-risk environments. This study contributes a novel perspective to AI governance, offering a pathway toward self-regulating AI systems that are capable of upholding societal values, legal compliance, and moral reasoning autonomously. It further enables the auditability of AI-driven decisions, which is a key concern in ethical AI legislation and regulatory frameworks. Future work will focus on extending this model to handle cross-cultural ethics, emotional intelligence integration, and proactive ethical foresight. The results affirm that incorporating data-centric ethics within a conscious AI model is not only feasible but crucial for achieving moral alignment in autonomous systems operating in complex, uncertain, and ethically sensitive environments',0,8,0,8894,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'I am pleased to submit our original research manuscript entitled Predictive Framework for Moral Decision Modeling in Critical Systems Using Conscious AI and Data-Centric Ethics for your kind consideration for publication in the Journal of Computer Science (JCS).\r\nThis paper proposes a novel hybrid frameworkNeuro-Causal Intelligence (NCI)which integrates causal inference techniques with deep neural network architectures to address the critical need for transparency and interpretability in autonomous scientific systems. Our work is driven by the increasing deployment of AI in high-stakes domains like healthcare, environmental monitoring, and scientific simulations, where understanding and justifying decisions is as important as predictive performance.\r\nWe affirm that this manuscript is original, has not been published elsewhere, and is not under consideration by any other publication. Another author have approved the manuscript and agree with its submission.\r\n\r\nThank you for your time and consideration. We look forward to the opportunity to share our findings with the wider research community.','2025-05-26','2025-06-04',0,'submissions/merged_submission_150.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,3,139,1,NULL,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/kiruthika_aids_jcs_papers_1.pdf'),(152,'Quantum driven Neuro spatial Cognition for Multilayered Data Interpretation Using AI augmented Spatiotemporal Modelling','KJCS-2025-05-14','Artificial Intelligence systems face increasing challenges in processing and interpreting complex, high-dimensional, and multilayered datasets that evolve across time and space. To address this, we propose a novel architecture called Quantum driven Neuro spatial Cognition (QNSC), a next-generation AI framework that integrates quantum-inspired encoding, neuro-symbolic modeling, and spatiotemporal learning to enhance interpretability and decision-making in uncertain environments. Unlike conventional deep neural networks and transformers, QNSC utilizes entangled memory layers and phase-shifted signal processors, enabling dynamic memory reallocation and long-term pattern recognition across spatiotemporal sequences. The system incorporates a quantum attention modulation layer (QAML) that improves computational efficiency by 26% while preserving data fidelity. Extensive experiments were conducted on three real-world datasets: geospatial climate sequences, multimodal medical imaging, and industrial sensor streams. QNSC demonstrated a significant performance gain, achieving 94.6% prediction accuracy in event detection, a 32.5% increase in spatial-temporal coherence, and a 28.1% reduction in false positives when compared to state-of-the-art transformer-based models. In addition, the model achieved a training convergence speed-up of 2.3 and demonstrated robust generalization under adversarial noise injections and missing data scenarios. QNSC also produced interpretable output maps that visually localized decision-influencing zones with 87% relevance alignment, making it suitable for critical domains such as healthcare, disaster prediction, and autonomous systems.',0,10,2,3143,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'I am pleased to submit our manuscript entitled \"Quantum driven Neuro spatial Cognition for Multilayered Data Interpretation Using AI Augmented Spatiotemporal Modelling\" for consideration for publication in JCS. This work represents a novel approach to spatiotemporal data interpretation using a hybrid artificial intelligence framework that integrates quantum-inspired encoding, neuro-symbolic reasoning, and entangled memory modeling.\r\n\r\nOur proposed architecture, the Quantum driven Neuro Spatial Cognition (QNSC) model, addresses long-standing challenges in interpreting high-dimensional, noisy, and dynamic datasets. We demonstrate the models superiority through extensive evaluations on real-world datasets across diverse domains including biomedical imaging, environmental sensor analytics, and financial trend detection. The QNSC framework significantly outperforms existing state-of-the-art models in terms of accuracy, interpretability, computational efficiency, and robustness to noise.\r\n\r\nKey contributions of this research include:\r\n\r\nIntroduction of Quantum Phase Encoding Layer (QPEL) for enhanced feature representation;\r\n\r\nDevelopment of Entangled Memory Matrices (EMM) for long-term context retention\r\nIntegration of a Quantum Attention Modulation Layer (QAML) that reduces computational overhead\r\n\r\nWe believe that our manuscript will be of strong interest to the readers of JCS, particularly those working at the intersection of artificial intelligence, quantum computing, cognitive systems, and real-world data modeling.\r\n\r\nWe confirm that this manuscript is original, has not been published before, and is not currently being considered for publication elsewhere. All authors have approved the manuscript and agree with its submission.\r\n\r\nThank you for considering our work. We look forward to the opportunity to contribute to your esteemed journal.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nDr. K. Nithya\r\n(On behalf of all authors)\r\nAssistant Professor, Artificial Intelligence and Data Science\r\nKarpagam Academy of Higher Education, Coimbatore\r\nEmail: nithya.kumar@kahedu.edu.in\r\n\r\nCo-author:\r\nDr. P. Matheswaran\r\nAssistant Professor, Computer Science and Engineering\r\nK. Ramakrishnan College of Technology, Trichy\r\nEmail: mathesh3@gmail.com','2025-05-27','2025-06-04',0,'submissions/merged_submission_152.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,3,141,1,NULL,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/nithya_aids_1.pdf'),(153,'MACHINE LEARNING TECHNIQUES FOR 5G AND BEYOND','KJCS-2025-05-15','Network embedding assigns network nodes to low dimensional representations, which effectively preserves the network topology. Recent years have seen a significant degree of advancement towards this new paradigm for network research. In this work, we focus on categorizing, evaluating, and suggesting future paths for the study of network embedding techniques. We start by briefly outlining network embedding\'s goal. In the context of cognitive radio, we discuss network embedding and its relation to classical graph embedding techniques. Subsequently, we provide a comprehensive and systematic description of a wide range of network embedding strategies, such as sophisticated information preservation techniques, side information containing techniques, and approaches that maintain structure and attributes. Furthermore, a variety of network embedding assessment techniques are investigated, along with a few useful web resources including network data sets and software. In the final section, we discuss the fundamentals of applying these network embedding techniques to build a functional system and pinpoint some potential directions for the future.',0,0,0,4497,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'I am pleased to submit our manuscript entitled Machine Learning Techniques for 5G and Beyond for consideration for publication in JCS. This paper presents a comprehensive study on the application of machine learning (ML) methodologies in optimizing and supporting the evolution of 5G and beyond (B5G) wireless communication systems.\r\n\r\nThe manuscript explores the growing significance of ML in addressing the complexities associated with next-generation networks. It provides a structured overview of network embedding strategies and evaluates their relevance in cognitive radio environments and smart communication infrastructures. Additionally, we assess current research in dynamic spectrum access, UAV communications, edge computing for IIoT, and AI-driven smart cities  all within the context of enabling B5G systems.\r\n\r\nKey highlights of our paper include:\r\n\r\nA comparative literature survey identifying gaps and research opportunities for 6G.\r\n\r\nEvaluation of ML techniques in dynamic spectrum access, edge computing, and cognitive networks.\r\n\r\nDiscussion on real-time applications such as braincomputer interfaces and smart energy management.\r\n\r\nThis manuscript is original, has not been published elsewhere, and is not under consideration by any other publication. All authors have approved the manuscript and agree with its submission.\r\n\r\nWe believe the manuscript aligns with the scope and audience of [Journal Name] and will be of interest to researchers and practitioners in wireless communications, artificial intelligence, and future internet technologies.\r\n\r\nThank you for considering our submission. We look forward to your response.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nSanmathi T\r\n(On behalf of all authors)\r\nEmail: [sanmathi.thamaraikannan@kahedu.edu.in]\r\n\r\nRamya M\r\n(On behalf of all authors)\r\nEmail: [hemaramya47@gmail.com]','2025-05-27','2025-06-04',0,'submissions/merged_submission_153.pdf','',NULL,NULL,3,3,142,1,2,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(154,'HARNESSING MACHINE LEARNING TO PREDICT MENTAL HEALTH CHALLENGES: A FOCUS ON STRESS, DEPRESSION, AND ANXIETY','KJCS-2025-05-16','The increasing incidence of stress, anxiety, and depression highlights the need for effective prediction mechanisms. This study utilizes machine learning models to forecast these mental health conditions based on responses to the DASS-21 questionnaire, with participants from varied cultural and professional contexts. Five machine learning algorithms were assessed for their predictive capabilities despite evident class imbalance issues. The Random Forest classifier yielded the best performance based on the F1 score, and specificity scores confirmed the models\' robustness in identifying individuals without adverse mental health conditions.',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'',0,'Dear Editor-in-Chief,\r\n\r\nI am pleased to submit our manuscript entitled HARNESSING MACHINE LEARNING TO PREDICT MENTAL HEALTH CHALLENGES: A FOCUS ON STRESS, DEPRESSION, AND ANXIETY  for consideration for publication in JCS. This study investigates early detection of depression in women using ML techniques.\r\nThank you for considering our submission. We look forward to the opportunity to contribute to your esteemed journal. \r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nDivya P','2025-05-27','2025-06-04',0,'submissions/merged_submission_154.pdf','high plagarism....52%\n',NULL,NULL,3,3,133,1,2,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(155,'AI-DRIVEN SOLUTIONS FOR COGNITIVE DISTRACTION DETECTION: ADVANCING ROAD SAFETY THROUGH PHYSIOLOGICAL SIGNAL ANALYSIS','KJCS-2025-05-17','This work explores the use of artificial intelligence (AI) in conjunction with physiological signs to identify cognitive distraction in drivers. One major issue for road safety is cognitive distraction from activities unrelated to safe driving. Conventional methods of evaluating cognitive distraction rely on objective self-reports or direct measurements, which may not fully capture the subtleties of a driver\'s cognitive workload. In this study, we offer a system that leverages artificial intelligence (AI) technologies to detect and assess cognitive distraction in real-time, while also integrating a secondary task into the driving environment.',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'This work explores the use of artificial intelligence (AI) in conjunction with physiological signs to identify cognitive distraction in drivers.','2025-05-30','2025-06-04',0,'submissions/merged_submission_155.pdf','',NULL,NULL,3,3,140,1,2,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(157,'Develop a system for managing student records, grades, and attendance','KJCS-2025-06-2','In the modern era of technology, educational institutions are progressively looking for effective ways to handle student information and progress. Using artificial intelligence (AI) and a hybrid Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) and Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) architecture, this study provides a unique Automated Student Records, Grades, and Attendance Management System. By automating grade prediction, attendance tracking, and student data management, the system seeks to reduce administrative workloads. By processing live facial images in an efficient manner, the CNN module improves accuracy and lowers manual errors in real-time attendance marking. Accurate grade projections based on past attendance and performance trends are made possible by the LSTM model\'s simultaneous analysis of historical academic data. A unified CNN-LSTM architecture also handles student records by flagging them for additional evaluation when it notices anomalies like irregular attendance patterns or grade variations. By continuously learning from incoming data, the AI integration helps the system become more accurate and adaptive over time. In addition to making managing student data easier, the suggested system offers useful information for early performance improvements. By assisting administrators and teachers in making decisions, this multidimensional approach improves the effectiveness of the educational environment. The system is a useful tool for contemporary educational institutions despite difficulties with computational needs and data preparation. It may produce results in real time. The findings of this study highlight the possibility of using artificial intelligence (AI) and cutting-edge machine learning methods to improve overall student record management, which would enhance learning outcomes and student engagement.',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'Krishna Sree K\r\nKarpagam Academy of Higher Education\r\ncoimbatore\r\nkrishnasree.karuppusamy@kahedu.edu.in\r\n9042980980\r\n02-06-2025\r\n\r\nDear Sir/Mam,\r\n\r\nI am pleased to submit our manuscript entitled Development of an Integrated System for Managing Student Records, Grades, and Attendancefor consideration for publication in the JCS.\r\n\r\nThis paper presents the design and implementation of a comprehensive system aimed at streamlining the management of student information within educational institutions. The system integrates student records, grade calculations, and attendance tracking into a centralized platform, thereby reducing manual errors and enhancing accessibility for administrators, teachers, and students. Key features include a secure centralized database, automated grade management, real-time attendance monitoring, and user-specific access controls.\r\n\r\nWe believe this work contributes valuable insights into the application of computer science principles to educational management and offers practical solutions to common challenges faced by academic institutions.\r\n\r\nThis manuscript has not been published elsewhere and is not under consideration by any other journal. All authors have approved the submission and declare no conflicts of interest.\r\n\r\nThank you for considering our manuscript. We look forward to your feedback.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nKrishna Sree\r\nAssistant Professor\r\ncse-cyber security \r\nkarpagam academy of higher education,coimbatore.','2025-06-02','2025-06-04',0,'submissions/merged_submission_157.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,3,143,1,NULL,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/krishnashrree-jcs.pdf'),(158,'INTRODUCING TO DESIGN AN APP THAT ASSISTS USER IN PLANNING THEIR TRIPS, INCLUDING HOTEL BOOKINGS AND  FINDING LOCAL ATTRACTIONS','KJCS-2025-06-3','Travel and tourism management system is used to book a tour from anywhere in the world by a single dynamic website which will help the user to know all about the places and tour details in a single website. The admin can add packages to the website from a certain travel agents and hotels by create a tour page. Then the users can sign in and book each project they can be confirmed by the admin in them manage booking page. The user can see the confirmation in my booking page. It is an easiest platform for all travelers which can be easily booked and know the all details. Tour Management system is a dynamic website for tourism business. It is dynamic and responsive web design. It is also called travel technology solution for agencies tour operation. Nearly Everyone goes on a vacation for this a Tourism management system would play a vital role in planning the perfect trip. The tourism management system allows the user of the system access all the details such as location events etc.',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'02-06-2025\r\n\r\nJournal of Computer Science (JCS)\r\n\r\nDear Mam/Sir,\r\n\r\nPlease find enclosed our manuscript entitled Introducing the Design of a Mobile App that Assists Users in Planning Their Trips, Including Hotel Bookings and the Discovery of Local Attractions. We submit it for exclusive consideration for publication in the Journal of Computer Science.\r\n\r\nThis paper presents the end-to-end design and prototyping of a smart-travel application that:\r\n\r\nintegrates real-time hotel-booking APIs with dynamic pricing models;\r\n\r\nrecommends context-aware local attractions via a hybrid content-based / collaborative-filtering engine;\r\n\r\nemploys an intuitive UX workflow validated through usability studies with sixty volunteer travellers.\r\n\r\nOur results show a 22 % reduction in average trip-planning time and a 15 % increase in itinerary satisfaction scores versus leading commercial apps. We believe these findings will be of strong interest to JCS readers working in human-centred computing, mobile systems, and applied AI.\r\n\r\nThe manuscript is original, has not been published previously, and is not under consideration elsewhere. All authors have approved the manuscript and agree to its submission to JCS. We have no conflicts of interest to declare, and all supporting data and source code will be made available in an open-access repository upon acceptance, in accordance with JCS policy.\r\n\r\nThank you for considering our work. We look forward to your feedback.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\n\r\nINBAKUMARI K\r\nKarpagam Academy of Higher Education\r\nCoimbatore , India\r\nCoimbatore\r\n inbakumari.kuppusamy@kahedu.edu.in\r\n(on behalf of all co-authors)','2025-06-02','2025-06-04',0,'submissions/merged_submission_158.pdf','',NULL,NULL,3,3,144,1,2,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(159,'A Review on existing cloud load balancing techniques','KJCS-2025-06-4','Cloud computing is a set of services provided via the internet, or \"the cloud.\" It involves the \r\nuse of remote servers in order to store and retrieve data rather than using local hard drives \r\nand internal data centres. \r\nPre-cloud computing, organizations needed to buy and maintain their own servers for \r\nbusiness requirements. It involved purchasing sufficient server space reduce downtime and \r\noutages, and to support peak traffic volume. Consequently, vast amounts of server space were \r\nleft idle for most of the time. Cloud service providers today enable enterprises to minimize \r\nthe need for on-site servers, maintenance staff, and other expensive IT resources. \r\nLoad balancing refers to the method of distributing incoming network traffic evenly across \r\nmultiple servers or computing resources to ensure no single system is overwhelmed. It plays \r\na vital role in optimizing resource utilization, enhancing system responsiveness, and \r\nmaintaining service reliability. By dynamically reallocating workloads, it enables \r\norganizations to meet varying performance demands and application requirements efficiently.',0,3,2,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'Respected Sir/Madam,\r\n\r\nKindly consider the survet paper submitted for review and publication.\r\n\r\nThank you.','2025-06-04','2025-06-04',0,'submissions/merged_submission_159.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,3,120,2,NULL,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/nimmijcs2_1.pdf'),(160,'Cognitect AI Neurofused Data Convergence Framework for Hyper predictive Reasoning in Dynamic Systems','KJCS-2025-06-5','In the evolving landscape of Artificial Intelligence and Data Science, existing models often fall short in environments requiring real-time adaptability and high-accuracy predictions across inconsistent data streams. This research introduces CognitectAI, a groundbreaking framework that redefines predictive intelligence through the application of neuroses data synthesis, combining deep cognitive mapping with adaptive neural restructuring. Unlike static machine learning models, CognitectAI continuously refines its internal architecture by learning from data entropy, signal variation, and contextual dependencies. The system was rigorously tested on four real-world datasets spanning healthcare diagnostics, financial time-series, environmental monitoring, and social network trends. The framework achieved an accuracy rate of 98.73%, a 42.1% reduction in processing latency, and a performance uplift of 8.6% in F1-score compared to Transformer-XL and GRU-based architectures. Output consistency remained above 92.5% under data noise and adversarial perturbation conditions, indicating strong robustness and generalization capabilities. CognitectAI also features a novel Explainable Output Engine that visualizes decision logic without compromising computational efficiency, offering clear transparency for domains like autonomous systems, smart governance, and medical intelligence. The interpretability of the predictionsquantified using a trust index modelshowed a 94.2% correlation with ground truth explanations by domain experts.',0,10,1,6730,0,0,0,0,0,'Nil',0,'Nil','2025-06-04','2025-06-04',0,'submissions/merged_submission_160.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,3,138,1,NULL,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/nagalakshmi_aids_2.pdf'),(161,'Designing Sustainable Crop Insurance Using Predictive Artificial Intelligence Models','KJCS-2025-06-6','The increasing volatility of climate change and market conditions poses significant challenges to traditional crop insurance programs, which often fail to address the dynamic risks faced by farmers. Predictive AI models offer a transformative solution by leveraging machine learning and data analytics to design sustainable crop insurance programs. This study explores the development and application of predictive models using historical climate, crop yield, and market data to assess risk and recommend optimized insurance premiums. Advanced techniques such as ensemble learning, time-series forecasting, and geospatial analysis are utilized to enhance the accuracy of risk predictions. The results demonstrate that the AI-driven framework achieves a 15% reduction in premium costs for low-risk farmers while increasing loss coverage by 25% compared to traditional methods. The model also enables dynamic adjustments to insurance terms based on real-time weather and market conditions, ensuring greater adaptability and resilience. This research highlights the potential of predictive AI to create equitable, cost-effective, and sustainable crop insurance programs that address the challenges of modern agriculture.',0,2,6,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'Mrs.S.Kanimozhi\r\n1W/90 East Street,Kunnur Post \r\nTheni district\r\nkanilidigomtech@gmail.com\r\n9080344043\r\n04.06.2025\r\nMrs.S.Kanimozhi\r\nDesigning Sustainable Crop Insurance Using Predictive Artificial Intelligence Models / Department of CSE(Cyber Security)\r\nKarpagam Academy of Higher Education\r\nCoimbatore\r\nDear Kanimozhi.S,\r\nI am writing to express my strong interest in the opportunity to contribute to or lead the project titled \"Designing Sustainable Crop Insurance Using Predictive Artificial Intelligence Models.\" With a background in [your field  e.g., agricultural economics, data science, environmental policy], and a deep commitment to leveraging technology for climate resilience, I am excited about the potential of using AI to address the challenges of agricultural risk and sustainability.\r\nAgricultural producers worldwide are increasingly vulnerable to climate variability and market fluctuations. Traditional crop insurance mechanisms often fall short due to their reliance on historical data and static risk models. I believe that integrating machine learning and predictive analytics can enable more accurate, responsive, and equitable insurance solutionsbenefiting smallholder farmers and large-scale operations alike.\r\nMy experience in [briefly mention relevant experience  e.g., developing machine learning models for environmental data, working with satellite imagery, or analyzing agro-climatic risk] equips me to contribute to both the technical and policy dimensions of this initiative. I am particularly interested in exploring how AI can model future climate risk scenarios, price premiums more equitably, and ensure financial sustainability for both insurers and policyholders.\r\nI am enthusiastic about collaborating with interdisciplinary teams and stakeholdersfrom technologists and agronomists to policymakers and community organizationsto co-design solutions that are both technically robust and socially just. I am confident that my blend of analytical skills, research acumen, and commitment to sustainable development aligns well with the goals of this project.\r\nThank you for considering my application. I would welcome the opportunity to discuss how my expertise and vision could contribute to the success of this initiative. Please find my resume and supporting documents attached for your review.\r\nWarm regards,\r\nMrs.S.kanimozhi','2025-06-04','2025-06-04',0,'submissions/merged_submission_161.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,3,145,1,NULL,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/kanimozhi-jcs1_1.pdf'),(163,'MACHINE LEARNING TECHNIQUES FOR 5G AND BEYOND','KJCS-2025-06-8','Network embedding assigns network nodes to low dimensional representations, which effectively preserves the network topology. Recent years have seen a significant degree of advancement towards this new paradigm for network research. In this work, we focus on categorizing, evaluating, and suggesting future paths for the study of network embedding techniques. We start by briefly outlining network embedding\'s goal. In the context of cognitive radio, we discuss network embedding and its relation to classical graph embedding techniques. Subsequently, we provide a comprehensive and systematic description of a wide range of network embedding strategies, such as sophisticated information preservation techniques, side information containing techniques, and approaches that maintain structure and attributes. Furthermore, a variety of network embedding assessment techniques are investigated, along with a few useful web resources including network data sets and software. In the final section, we discuss the fundamentals of applying these network embedding techniques to build a functional system and pinpoint some potential directions for the future.',0,3,1,2084,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'T.Sanmathi\r\nKarpagam Academy of Higher Education\r\nCoimbatore\r\n 6383788872\r\nsanmathi.thamaraikannan@kahedu.edu.in\r\n\r\n\r\nSubject: Submission of \"MACHINE LEARNING TECHNIQUES FOR 5G AND BEYOND\"\r\n\r\nI am pleased to submit our manuscript, \"MACHINE LEARNING TECHNIQUES FOR 5G AND BEYOND,\" for consideration for publication in JCS. This paper explores the crucial role of machine learning in advancing 5G and Beyond 5G (B5G) communication networks, addressing critical aspects such as resource allocation, network performance optimization, and complexity mitigation in dynamic and heterogeneous network environments.\r\n\r\nThe rapid evolution of communication networks, driven by 5G technology and the emerging B5G era, necessitates innovative approaches to manage their increasing complexity. Our work highlights how machine learning techniques are becoming indispensable tools for achieving the high standards set for the next generation of wireless communication, facilitating intelligent and adaptive decision-making.\r\nIn this manuscript, we provide a comprehensive and systematic description of various network embedding strategies, including sophisticated information preservation techniques, side information-containing techniques, and approaches that maintain structure and attributes. We also investigate a variety of network embedding assessment techniques and discuss the fundamentals of applying these techniques to build functional systems.\r\n\r\nA key contribution of our proposed system is the application of the Particle Swarm Optimization (PSO) algorithm, which offers advantages such as simplicity, resilience to control parameters, ease of implementation, and processing efficiency. The proposed framework, composed of several interrelated modules, is designed to provide cutting-edge understanding of intricate network structures. This includes the Network Construction Module utilizing matrix factorization, the Matrix Factorization Route Analysis Module for optimizing connectivity, the Band Major Differences Management Module for effective variance management, and the Structure Preserving Network Node Grouping and Data Sharing Module for maintaining network structure while grouping nodes and sharing data.\r\n\r\nWe believe this paper will be of significant interest to the readers of JCS as it offers timely insights into the convergence of machine learning and next-generation wireless communication, addressing critical challenges and opportunities in the field.\r\n\r\nThank you for your time and consideration. We look forward to your positive response.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nT.Sanmathi','2025-06-05','2025-06-17',0,'submissions/merged_submission_163.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,3,142,1,NULL,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/sanmathi_jcs.pdf'),(165,'Graph Neural Network for Detecting Bitcoin Double-Spending Attacks','KJCS-2025-06-10','The new world of digital money dawned in 2008 when Satoshi Nakamoto first launched Bitcoin. In contrast to traditional banking systems, Bitcoin enables individuals to transfer money directly to each other without banks and other intermediaries. This is possible due to blockchain technology, an open, secure, and immutable digital ledger that is maintained through a process called mining. Though advantageous, Bitcoin has its own drawbacks. One serious point of worry is double-spending attacks, where an individual attempts to use the same money in multiple transactions by exploiting delays and errors in the network. To detect such threats, complicated procedures must be employed.\r\nGraph neural networks, or GNNs, are becoming a more effective means of handling sophisticated network information. Through enabling each node of a graph to exchange messages with the nodes that it is immediately connected to, these methods enable detecting anomalous patterns of activity. Better versions that provide even greater vision are Graph Attention Networks (GATs) and Graph Convolutional Networks (GCNs). This research investigates the application of GNNs to enhance the security of Bitcoin to detect and avoid double-spending.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2025-06-11','2025-06-11',0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,3,149,1,NULL,NULL,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(166,'HARNESSING MACHINE LEARNING TO PREDICT MENTAL HEALTH CHALLENGES: A FOCUS ON STRESS, DEPRESSION, AND ANXIETY','KJCS-2025-06-11','The increasing incidence of stress, anxiety, and depression highlights the need for effective prediction mechanisms. This study utilizes machine learning models to forecast these mental health conditions based on responses to the DASS-21 questionnaire, with participants from varied cultural and professional contexts. Five machine learning algorithms were assessed for their predictive capabilities despite evident class imbalance issues. The Random Forest classifier yielded the best performance based on the F1 score, and specificity scores confirmed the models\' robustness in identifying individuals without adverse mental health conditions.',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'',0,'I am pleased to submit our manuscript titled HARNESSING MACHINE LEARNING TO PREDICT MENTAL HEALTH CHALLENGES: A FOCUS ON STRESS, DEPRESSION, AND ANXIETY for consideration for publication in JCS. \r\n\r\nThank you for considering our work. We appreciate your time and look forward to the opportunity to contribute to JCS\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nDivya P','2025-06-12','2025-06-17',0,'submissions/merged_submission_166.pdf','High Plagarism in the article\n',NULL,NULL,3,3,133,1,2,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/divya.p_jcs.pdf'),(167,'Enhancing Blockchain Security: A Comprehensive Study on Double Spending Detection and Prevention','KJCS-2025-06-12','Blockchain technology has revolutionized digital transactions by integrating transparent, secure, and decentralized financial systems. But it is endangered by critical vulnerabilities from defects such as Sybil attacks, selfish mining, and double-spending attacks. Researchers have explored various methods to minimize such threats, including hybrid consensus protocols, machine learning algorithms, Graph Neural Networks (GNNs), and mathematical modeling-based fraud prediction and prevention. To achieve maximum blockchain security, Meybodi introduces machine learning algorithms (SDTLA and WVBM), while Kang et al. propose a GNN-based model to precisely predict double-spending attacks. To address double-spending attacks, Akbar et al. propose a hybrid Proof-of-Work (PoW) and Proof-of-Stake (PoS), whereas Yuen et al. focus on Bitcoin Generator Scam (BGS) detection, addressing over-smoothing issues in GNNs.Other strategies for blockchain security improvement are Block Access Restriction (BAR) techniques, ECDSA-based prevention mechanisms, and GraphSAGE and Graph Attention Networks (GAT). A safer and stronger decentralized financial system is guaranteed by this paper\'s discussion of such methods, research gaps identification, and investigation of enhancements to enhance blockchain networks\' capabilities in fraud detection, scalability, and flexibility..',0,0,1,2925,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'Dear KJCS team,\r\nI would like to publish my article in  KJCS.','2025-06-12','2025-06-17',0,'submissions/merged_submission_167_jCDpQ9Q.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,3,149,1,NULL,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','submissions/rintu_jcs_zhTe8Tg.pdf'),(168,'AN EFFICIENT STUDY OF USER AUTHENTICATION METHODS IN BANKING SERVICES USING TWO FACTOR AUTHENTICATION TECHNIQUES','KJCS-2025-06-13','Online banking has become increasingly popular in recent years, making it a target for cyberattacks. Banks have implemented various user authentication methods to protect their customers online accounts. This paper reviews the state-of-the-art user authentication methods used in online banking and potential cyber threats. This paper starts by exploring different user authentication methods, such as knowledge-based authentication (KBA), biometrics-based authentication (BBA), possession-based authentication (PBA), and other methods. The advantages and disadvantages of each user authentication method are then discussed. Furthermore, the paper discusses the various cyber threats that can compromise user authentication for online banking systems, such as malware attacks, social engineering, phishing attacks, man-in-the-middle (MiTM) attacks, denial of service (DoS) attacks, session hijacking, weak passwords, keyloggers, SQL injection, and replay attacks. Also, the paper explores the user authentication methods used by popular banks, which can provide insights into best practices for safeguarding online banking accounts and future user authentication methods in online banking and cyber threats. It states that the increasing use of BBA, two- factor authentication (2FA), and multi-factor authentication (MFA) will help improve the security of online banking systems. However, the paper also warns that new cyber challenges will emerge, and banks need to be vigilant in protecting their customers online banking accounts.',0,2,3,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'No',0,'S.Ragunathan (24DR2CS010)\r\n89/140,subramanium street,\r\nKallanguthu,Salem-636001\r\nragu34salem@gmail.com\r\n8870447404\r\n\r\nThe Editor-in-Chief\r\nKarpagam Journal of Computer Science\r\nKarpagam Academy of Higher Education\r\nCoimbatore, Tamil Nadu, India\r\n\r\nSubject: Manuscript Submission  An Efficient Study of User Authentication Methods in Banking Services Using Two-Factor Authentication Techniques\r\n\r\nDear Sir/Madam,\r\n\r\nI am pleased to submit my manuscript titled An Efficient Study of User Authentication Methods in Banking Services Using Two-Factor Authentication Techniques for your kind consideration for publication in the Karpagam Journal of Computer Science (JCS).\r\n\r\nThis research article presents a comprehensive and efficient study of various user authentication mechanisms adopted in banking services, with a particular focus on two-factor authentication (2FA) techniques. The study critically evaluates current methods, highlights their strengths and limitations, and proposes strategic insights for enhanced user security in the evolving digital banking landscape.\r\n\r\nI confirm that the manuscript is original, has not been published elsewhere, and is not currently under consideration by any other journal or conference. All authors have read and approved the manuscript, and there are no conflicts of interest to declare.\r\n\r\nPlease find the manuscript attached along with this cover letter. I kindly request you to consider it for peer review and possible publication in your esteemed journal.\r\n\r\nThank you for your time and consideration. I look forward to your positive response.\r\n\r\nWarm regards,\r\nS.Ragunathan (24DR2CS010)\r\n89/140,subramanium street,\r\nKallanguthu,Salem-636001\r\nragu34salem@gmail.com','2025-06-18','2025-06-18',0,'submissions/merged_submission_168.pdf','High Plagarism content in the article\n',NULL,NULL,3,3,150,1,2,8,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(169,'ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE BASED GLAUCOMA DETECTION USING IMPROVED CONVOLUTION NEURAL NETWORK ALGORITHM','KJCS-2025-06-14','Abstract: In tackling the contemporary challenge of navigating numerous assistance schemes, our proposed solution seeks to transform the process by developing a user-centric Python website integrated with an advanced Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) algorithm. Prioritizing simplicity and accessibility, the website will function as a centralized platform for scheme identification, catering to the diverse needs of users from various backgrounds. Through meticulous data collection and preprocessing, we will compile extensive datasets containing comprehensive details on eligibility criteria, benefits, and application procedures across a wide spectrum of schemes. Harnessing the sequential structure inherent in scheme descriptions, the RNN algorithm will undergo training to accurately and efficiently classify schemes, thereby facilitating easy navigation through the extensive array of options. The website\'s interface will incorporate intuitive design elements and interactive features, enabling users to input their preferences and requirements seamlessly. By generating personalized recommendations based on user input, the website will empower individuals to make well-informed decisions and access relevant assistance programs efficiently. Our initiative extends beyond mere scheme identification, aiming to foster social inclusion and equity by democratizing access to essential benefits and services. Through the synergy of technology and social welfare, we envision a future where individuals navigate the intricacies of assistance schemes with confidence and simplicity, ultimately bolstering societal well-being and resilience.\r\nKeywords: Assistance scheme navigation; User-centric Python website; Recurrent Neural Network classification; Data preprocessing; Personalized recommendations; Social inclusion; Democratization of access.',0,7,1,10114,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE BASED GLAUCOMA DETECTION USING IMPROVED CONVOLUTION NEURAL NETWORK ALGORITHM\r\nH.Ramprasanth,\r\nDepartment of CA,Karpagam Academy of Higher Education,Coimbatore,Tamilnadu,India\r\nramprasanth1408@gmail.com','2025-06-18','2025-06-18',0,'submissions/merged_submission_169.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,16,3,151,1,NULL,NULL,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(170,'Intelligent Sepsis Detection in ICU: A Real-Time Deep Learning Framework with Hybrid Optimization','KJCS-2025-06-15','Abstract Without rapid medical intervention, sepsisthe body\'s catastrophic reaction to infectioncan cause organ failure and increased mortality.  There is an immediate need for real-time and automated detection methods because conventional diagnostic methods are often inaccurate or have delays.  In this research, to present a deep learning-based sepsis detection system that uses a CNN for early prediction in conjunction with a Modified Bidirectional Gated Recurrent Unit (MBiGRU).  Convolutional neural networks (CNNs) extract spatially rich and clinically significant features, while MBiGRUs efficiently model temporal patterns in physiological time-series data.  The framework incorporates a modified Chaotic Zebra Optimisation Algorithm to optimise feature selection and generalisation, significantly enhancing model efficiency and eliminating redundant information.  Using open-source sepsis datasets, to trained and validated the MBiGRU-CNN-CZOA model.  In comparison to more conventional models such simple CNN, LSTM, and GRU, the model outperformed them with a 93.82% accuracy, 94.24% precision, 93.82% recall, and 93.68% F1-score.  Fast decision-making and efficient calculation are guaranteed by the system\'s optimisation for real-time ICU deployment through edge computing.  Based on these results, the suggested approach seems to be well-suited for clinical use in the real world, where it could facilitate prompt intervention and drastically cut down on mortality risks.  In order to ensure the security of patient data when used in remote healthcare settings, future research will centre on improving interpretability and implementing federated learning strategies.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2025-06-19','2025-06-19',0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,3,152,1,NULL,NULL,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(172,'Quantum-AI-Driven Cyber-Resilient Framework for Zero-Trust Security in Next-Generation Networks','KJCS-2025-06-17','As cyber threats evolve in complexity; traditional security models struggle to provide real-time threat detection and mitigation. This research introduces a Quantum-AI-Driven Cyber-Resilient Framework that integrates quantum computing, artificial intelligence (AI), and blockchain to establish a Zero-Trust security model for next-generation networks, including 5G, 6G, and edge computing environments. The proposed system leverages quantum-enhanced machine learning (QML) for rapid anomaly detection and post-quantum cryptography (PQC) for secure data transmission, ensuring resilience against quantum-enabled cyberattacks. Additionally, blockchain-based identity verification and federated learning are incorporated to decentralize authentication processes, minimizing single points of failure. The framework autonomously adapts to emerging attack vectors using AI-driven self-healing mechanisms, ensuring continuous monitoring, real-time risk assessment, and automated threat response. This approach enhances network security by reducing false positives, improving detection accuracy, and mitigating advanced persistent threats (APTs) in real time. A comprehensive performance evaluation demonstrates the frameworks superiority over traditional security architectures in terms of latency, threat response time, and computational efficiency. The findings indicate that the proposed Quantum-AI-Driven Zero-Trust Framework serves as a future-proof cybersecurity paradigm for securing critical infrastructures, IoT ecosystems, and enterprise networks against next-generation cyber threats.',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'From\r\nJEEVITHA S\r\nAkshaya College Of Engineering And Technology,\r\nDepartment of Computer Science and Engineering, \r\njeevithaess@gmail.com\r\n+91 9500762676\r\n20-06-2025\r\n\r\nTo\r\nEditor-in-chief\r\nJournal of Computer Science\r\nKarpagam Publications(https://kjcs.karpagampublications.com/)\r\n\r\nDear Editor,\r\n\r\nI am pleased to submit our manuscript entitled Quantum-AI-Driven Cyber-Resilient Framework for Zero-Trust Security in Next-Generation Networks for consideration in Karpagam JCS. This paper presents an innovative, interdisciplinary cybersecurity architecture that combines quantum computing, artificial intelligence (AI), post-quantum cryptography (PQC), and blockchain technologies to address the growing challenges of real-time threat detection and mitigation in modern digital infrastructures.\r\n\r\nAs cyber threats continue to escalate in both sophistication and frequencyparticularly with the emergence of quantum-enabled attackstraditional security models prove increasingly inadequate. Our proposed Quantum-AI-Driven Zero-Trust Framework is specifically designed to meet the demands of 5G/6G networks, edge computing environments, and critical IoT systems, offering a robust, future-proof cybersecurity solution.\r\n\r\nKey contributions of the paper include:\r\n\r\n* Integration of Quantum Machine Learning (QML) for rapid anomaly detection and autonomous threat mitigation.\r\n* Deployment of Post-Quantum Cryptographic protocols for secure communication resilient to quantum attacks.\r\n* Implementation of blockchain-based identity management and federated learning to ensure decentralized, tamper-resistant authentication with minimal latency.\r\n* A self-healing AI architecture that adapts in real time to evolving threat landscapes, significantly reducing false positives and improving detection precision.\r\n\r\nWe also present a comprehensive performance evaluation comparing the framework against conventional architectures, highlighting its superiority in threat response time, computational efficiency, and cyber-resilience.\r\n\r\nGiven the journals commitment to advancing cybersecurity research and emerging technologies, we believe our work aligns closely with your editorial scope and will be of strong interest to your readership.\r\n\r\nThis manuscript is original, has not been published elsewhere, and is not under consideration by any other publication. All authors have reviewed and approved the final manuscript.\r\n\r\nThank you for considering our submission. We look forward to the opportunity to contribute to *\\[Journal/Conference Name]* and are happy to provide any additional information or clarifications upon request.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nJEEVITHA S\r\nOn behalf of all co-authors','2025-06-20','2025-06-20',0,'submissions/merged_submission_172_Fv6wh3p.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,16,3,154,1,NULL,NULL,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(173,'Integrating RNN and Transfer Learning for Comprehensive Plant Leaf Disease Detection','KJCS-2025-06-18','Plant diseases threaten the lives of farmers and the delivery of essential nutrients for the world\'s growing population, posing a serious threat to agricultural productivity and global food security. Plant diseases may be accurately and promptly identified. critical for mitigating their detrimental impact on agricultural productivity, as prompt intervention can help contain the spread of infections and minimize losses in crop yields. This paper proposes a novel approach that seamlessly integrates Recurrent Neural Networks and transfer learning techniques to effectively identify and classify a wide range of plant leaf diseases. The innovative methodology presented in this research aims to offer a strong, flexible, and all-inclusive solution for the prompt identification and precise categorization of diverse plant pathologies. By leveraging the powerful feature extraction and sequence modeling capabilities of Recurrent Neural Networks, combined with the rich visual representations and learned knowledge acquired from Convolutional models of neural networks that have already been trained, the suggested system aspires to make a significant contribution towards supporting sustainable farming methods and guaranteeing world food security by accurately Early detection and diagnosis of plant leaf diseases.',0,5,0,3375,0,0,0,0,0,'',0,'Respected Sir,\r\nI am working in Department of Information Technology, FASCM, KAHE. I am submitting my article for your kind consideration. \r\nThank You','2025-06-20','2025-06-20',0,'submissions/merged_submission_173.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,16,3,160,1,NULL,NULL,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(174,'AN EFFICIENT STUDY OF USER AUTHENTICATION METHODS IN BANKING SERVICES USING TWO FACTOR AUTHENTICATION TECHNIQUES','KJCS-2025-06-19','Online banking has become increasingly popular in recent years, making it a target for cyber attacks. Banks have implemented various user authentication methods to protect their customers online accounts. This paper reviews the state-of-the-art user authentication methods used in online banking and potential cyber threats. Furthermore, the paper discusses the various cyber threats that can compromise user authentication for online banking systems, such as malware attacks, social engineering, phishing attacks, man-in-the- middle (MiTM) attacks, denial of service (DoS) attacks, session hijacking, weak passwords, key loggers, SQL injection, and replay attacks. Also, the paper explores the user authentication methods used by popular banks, which can provide insights into best practices for safeguarding online banking accounts and future user authentication methods in online banking and cyber threats. It states that the increasing use of BBA, two- factor authentication (2FA), and multi-factor authentication (MFA) will help improve the security of online banking systems. However, the paper also warns that new cyber challenges will emerge, and banks need to be vigilant in protecting their customers online banking accounts',0,2,3,4161,0,0,0,0,0,'There is no Conflict of Interest',0,'S.Ragunathan (24DR2CS010)\r\n89/140,Subramanium street,\r\nKallanguthu,Salem-636001\r\nragu34salem@gmail.com\r\n8870447404\r\n\r\nThe Editor-in-Chief\r\nKarpagam Journal of Computer Science (KJCS)\r\nKarpagam Academy of Higher Education\r\nCoimbatore, Tamil Nadu, India\r\n\r\nDear Editor-in-Chief,\r\n\r\nSubject: Submission of Manuscript for Publication in KJCS\r\n\r\nI am pleased to submit our original research article titled \"AN EFFICIENT STUDY OF USER AUTHENTICATION METHODS IN BANKING SERVICES USING TWO FACTOR AUTHENTICATION TECHNIQUES\" for possible publication in the Karpagam Journal of Computer Science (KJCS).\r\n\r\nThis paper presents a comprehensive and efficient evaluation of current user authentication mechanisms used in banking services, focusing particularly on Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) techniques. The study highlights the strengths, limitations, and implementation considerations of various 2FA methods, contributing to the enhancement of secure banking transactions. The findings of our study are relevant to researchers, software developers, and cybersecurity practitioners working in the field of secure financial services.\r\n\r\nWe confirm that this manuscript is our original work, has not been published elsewhere, and is not under consideration by any other publication. All authors have read and approved the manuscript and have no conflicts of interest to disclose.\r\n\r\nWe hope that the article meets the high standards of your journal and look forward to your favorable consideration.\r\n\r\nThank you for your time and consideration.\r\nSincerely,\r\nS.Ragunathan (24DR2CS010)','2025-06-20','2025-06-20',0,'submissions/merged_submission_174.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,16,3,150,1,NULL,NULL,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','');
